description: Ensure cubic API key is configured before using cubic tools
alwaysApply: true
---

cubic-api-key:

- The cubic plugin requires a `CUBIC_API_KEY` environment variable (starts with `cbk_`).
- If cubic MCP tools return authentication errors, prompt the user to set up their key.
- Never log, display, or commit API keys. Treat `cbk_*` values as secrets.
- Direct users to https://www.cubic.dev/settings?tab=integrations&integration=mcp to generate keys.
